claim.claim-text:
A method for performing bit adaptive precoding matrix indicator (PMI) feedbacks adapted for an eNodeB (eNB) (101) having a fixed codebook (107) with fixed precoder indexes with each precoder index pointing to a specific precoder, and the method comprising:
receiving a PMI bit sequence (S 1102);
mapping the PMI bit sequence into a first precoder based on a bit mapping table and a reference precoder (S1103);
determining the next precoder by referencing the first precoder (S 1103); and
processing downlink data using the next precoder (S1104).

The method of claim 7 further comprising:
determining the quantity of NACK signals received;
if the received quantity of NACK signals exceeds a first threshold, transmit a second signal to re-configure the candidate set table and the bit mapping table.

The method of claim 18 further comprising:
monitoring the quantity of NACK signals transmitted;
if the transmitted quantity of NACK signals exceeds a first threshold, transmit a second signal to re-configure the candidate set table and the bit mapping table.
